-THREE WAYS OF USING CSS
--> inline style                 <p style='color: red; font-size: 20px;'>I'm learning to code!</p>

--> internal stylesheet 
<head>
  <title>Vacation World</title>
  <style>
    p {
      color:green;
    }
    </style>
</head>

--> linking the css file         <link href='./style.css' rel='stylesheet'>



- an universal type selector that targets all the elements 
             *{
             border: 1px solid red; }


- you can choose a class element by:
-->         <p class='brand'>Sole Shoe Company</p>
-->         .brand { }


p:hover {                                                      //hover is a pseudo-class, when you hover your mouse above the text 
  background-color: lime;                                      //the backround color will turn lime
} 
--> other pseudo classes are :focus, :visited, :disabled, and :active



h1, 
.menu {                                                        //here you have chosen class element menu and all h1 to be a specific font
  font-family: Georgia;
}

- making text uppercase     -->       text-transform: uppercase;
- making the text cursive   -->       font-family: cursive;
- border to a text or img   -->       border: 1px solid red;
- text color                -->       color:green;
- takes the href elements   -->       [href]{    color: magenta;    }
- takes a specific image    -->       img[src*='winter'] {                  //finds an image with 'winter' in the address
- targets link addresses    -->       a[href*='florence'] {
- sets a backround color    -->       background-color: aqua;
- chooses special classes h1 ->       h1.special {     }
- gets all li:s from mainlist >       .main-list li {     }
- targeting values with id  -->       #banner {     }



- - - - - - - - - - - - - -  - - - - - - -  -- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -


- you can change the text display by using                       -->        font-family: Helvetica
- font size can be modified using pixels, for example            -->        font-size: 18px
- regulating the thinness/boldness of text                       -->        font-weight: bold;     (has also value normal)
- aligns text on the screen                                      -->        text-align: right;     (left, right, center, justify)
- choosing color is made with these commands                     -->        color: red;
                                                                            background-color: blue;
- the opacity(visibility) can be changed with opacity(fading)    -->        opacity: 0.5;
- overriding all other rules with important                      -->        color: blue !important;
- targeting size                                                 -->        height: 18px   ->    widht: 25px  (can be 100%)
- targeting the border (width, style color)                      -->        border: 3px solid coral;
- curving the borders corners                                    -->        border-radius: 5px;
- targeting the padding                                          -->        padding: 15px
- targeting the margin (outside the border)                      -->        margin: 25px
- setting limits to size                                         -->        min-width:300px;  ->   max-width: 500px;
- a default value for overflowing content (visible)              -->        overflow: visible; 

--> the width can be pixels or thin, thick, medium / there are 10 styles / there are 140 built-in colors
--> you can create a circle by making height and width the same, border-radius 50%
--> you can change the padding on all sides -> padding-top, padding-bottom, padding-right, padding-left
--> padding: 6px 11px 4px 9px; (targets top, right, left, bottom)
--> padding: 5px 10px 20px;    (targets top, left/right, bottom)
--> padding: 5px 10px;         (targets top/bottom, left/right)
--> margin can also be set for all the sides, similarly to the padding 
--> horisontal margins add up, vertical ones collapse
--> overflow also has values: scroll and hidden 


- changing the elements backround 
-> .main-banner {
  background-image: url('images/mountains.jpg');
  }
  
- width: 400px;                     //in order to center an element, the width needs to be implemented
  margin: 0 auto;                   // this sets the top and bottom margin to 0 and centers the element automatically
  
- * {                               //like here you can reset the box-model in order to avoid sizing issues and overflowing
  box-sizing: border-box;           // you can also set margin and padding to 0 at the start of the file, for all elements
} 



