-------------POSITION 

- you can change an elements default position                --> position: static   (default value)

.green-box {
  background-color: green;       
  position: relative;              //we can position the element in relation to its default position
  top: 50px;                       // will move the element 50px down
  left: 120px;                     // will move the element 120px to the right
}

position: absolute;             //will place the element relative to the closest parent element (other elements will ignore it) 
                                //you can specify the position with top, right etc. It will move when the user is scrolling
                                
.title {
  position: fixed;              //you can set an element to be fixed, it wont move when scrolling, for example a navigation bar
  top: 0px;
  left: 0px;
}

.box-bottom {
  position: sticky;             //the position will move while scrolling, but then sticking to a specific location               
  top: 240px;
}

-  z-index: 1;                 //tells the depth of an element and decides which one will be layered on the website
                               //the higher the index, lower numbers wont come on top of it 


-------------DISPLAY

- display allows making every element inline, like a, em or strong's default value
- inline elements are wrapped in a thight box and can be directly next to each other, their height and width cannot be changed 

- block-level elements take the entire width of the page by default and are the height they need to display their content 
- these elements width can be made smaller 

- inline-block combines the inline and block. They can be next to each other and their size can be changed

- float: right;     //will move an element so far right as possible (left is also a value of float)
- you can use clear to make sure the elements don't bump into each other

- clear: left;      --> left side wont touch any other element (same for right) 
--> both    --> neither side will touch anything 
--> none    --> the element can touch all the sides  



